---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Consulting" description="Behavioral governance, trust architecture, and restraint specification for teams building with AI agents. Audits, workshops, implementation, and advisory.">
  <div class="hero">
    <h1>Everyone is talking about how to run more agents faster.</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Nobody is talking about how to run them well.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="container">
    <p>
      AI capabilities are outpacing adoption. Most organizations can build agents
      that work - fewer can build agents that work <em>well</em>, consistently, at scale,
      under real constraints. The gap between what's possible and what's deployed is where
      the real work lives. I help you see the gap clearly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Why Organizations Get Stuck</h2>
    <p>Four forces keep capable teams from deploying AI well.</p>

    <div class="inertia-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Regulatory</h3>
        <p>COPPA, HIPAA, GDPR. Rules written for a world before agents. Procurement cycles measured in years, not sprints.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Organizational</h3>
        <p>18 months from "this saves $10M/year" to saving it. Pilot programs, change management, internal politics.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Cultural</h3>
        <p>Most teams treat AI as a tool, not a discipline. Adoption requires muscle memory, not just better models.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Trust</h3>
        <p>Verification at scale is expensive. Moving from "I do the work" to "I verify AI work" requires guardrails and oversight infrastructure.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>How We Work</h2>
    <p>Four disciplines, each building on the last.</p>

    <div class="discipline-stack">
      <div class="level-card">
        <div class="level-number">1</div>
        <div class="level-content">
          <h3>Prompt Craft</h3>
          <p>Clear instructions, examples, guardrails. This is where most teams start - and where most teams stop. It's necessary, but not sufficient.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="level-card">
        <div class="level-number">2</div>
        <div class="level-content">
          <h3>Context Engineering</h3>
          <p>Curating the information environment agents operate within. System prompts, memory architecture, MCP servers, retrieval design.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="level-card">
        <div class="level-number">3</div>
        <div class="level-content">
          <h3>Intent Engineering</h3>
          <p>Encoding organizational purpose, values, and decision boundaries into agent infrastructure. Not what agents <em>can</em> do - what they <em>should</em> do.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="level-card">
        <div class="level-number">4</div>
        <div class="level-content">
          <h3>Specification Engineering</h3>
          <p>Writing documents autonomous agents can execute against over extended time horizons. The difference between a demo and a deployment.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="bridge-text">
      Most organizations are strong at Level 1, aware of Level 2, and have never considered
      Levels 3 and 4. We help you see the full stack.
    </p>
    <p class="bridge-text">
      Built in practice, not in theory. These frameworks come from a live multi-agent system we operate daily.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>In Practice</h2>
    <p>These frameworks come from live systems, not whiteboards.</p>

    <a href="/case-studies/labyrinth" class="case-study-card">
      <div class="case-study-header">
        <span class="badge">Case Study</span>
        <span class="case-study-collab">Builder: <strong>DaxxSec</strong></span>
      </div>
      <h3>Trust Architecture in the Wild</h3>
      <p>
        An independent defensive AI security platform analyzed through the four pillars
        of trust architecture. Identity as a defensive surface, memory with governance,
        structured authority, and refusal as architecture - not a feature.
      </p>
      <div class="case-study-stats">
        <span>5 defense layers</span>
        <span>5 AI providers intercepted</span>
        <span>4 operational modes</span>
      </div>
      <span class="case-study-link">Read the full case study</span>
    </a>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Start Here</h2>
    <p>Start where you are. Go as deep as you need.</p>

    <div class="ladder">
      <div class="ladder-step">
        <div class="ladder-marker">
          <span class="ladder-label">Self-serve</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ladder-content">
          <h3>Digital Products</h3>
          <p>Sovereignty assessment, trust architecture, voice design, governance, restraint, and memory frameworks. Use them on your own schedule.</p>
          <span class="ladder-price">$49 - $149</span>
          <a href="/products" class="ladder-link">Browse products</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ladder-step">
        <div class="ladder-marker">
          <span class="ladder-label">Evaluate</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ladder-content">
          <h3>Fit Assessment</h3>
          <p>5-minute assessment to figure out which engagement type matches where you are right now. No commitment, no sales call required.</p>
          <span class="ladder-price">Free</span>
          <a href="/fit" class="ladder-link">Take the assessment</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ladder-step">
        <div class="ladder-marker">
          <span class="ladder-label">Audit</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ladder-content">
          <h3>Governance Audit</h3>
          <p>A structured review of your agent system's behavioral governance - identity, memory, restraint, voice, and drift. Delivered as a prioritized findings report with implementation roadmap. This is where most engagements start.</p>
          <span class="ladder-price">$3,000 - $10,000</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ladder-step">
        <div class="ladder-marker">
          <span class="ladder-label">Build</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ladder-content">
          <h3>Implementation</h3>
          <p>Hands-on work with your team - specification sprints, trust architecture builds, restraint specification development, agent identity design. Scope and timeline defined by audit findings.</p>
          <span class="ladder-price">$5,000 - $150,000</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ladder-step">
        <div class="ladder-marker">
          <span class="ladder-label">Sustain</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ladder-content">
          <h3>Advisory Retainer</h3>
          <p>Ongoing governance partner. Monthly reviews, drift monitoring, specification updates, and strategic counsel as your agent system evolves.</p>
          <span class="ladder-price">$5,000 - $15,000/mo</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Services</h2>

    <div class="guarantee">
      <strong>The Guarantee:</strong> If an assessment or audit doesn't surface at least 3 actionable findings, you pay nothing.
    </div>

    <h3>Governance Audits</h3>
    <div class="services-list">
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Agent Governance Audit <span class="discipline-badge">Full Practice</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">Comprehensive review of behavioral governance - how agents decide, refuse, and respect boundaries across identity, memory, restraint, and voice. Delivered as findings report + implementation roadmap.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$7,500</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Four-Discipline Audit</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Evaluate your team's prompt craft, context engineering, intent engineering, and specification maturity. Lighter-weight assessment focused on capability gaps.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,500</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Context Engineering Review <span class="discipline-badge">Context Engineering</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">Audit your agent memory, retrieval, system prompts, and information environment.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Sovereignty Assessment</div>
        <div class="service-desc">47-point assessment of your product across 7 domains. Independently facilitated - you get the score and the story behind it.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Privacy Architecture Review</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Map your data flows, consent patterns, encryption coverage, and minimization gaps. Delivered as a prioritized findings report.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Security Code Review</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Audit authentication, session management, encryption implementation, and rate limiting. Delivered as a fixes list ranked by severity.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,500</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">COPPA Technical Review</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Assess your age-gating, parental consent flows, data collection, and retention against current COPPA requirements. Delivered as an implementation roadmap.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,500</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="mt-lg">Workshops</h3>
    <div class="services-list">
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Trust Architecture Workshop <span class="discipline-badge">Full Practice</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">Full-day guided implementation of all four trust pillars on your agent system with your team. You see it in the room.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$8,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Intent Engineering Workshop <span class="discipline-badge">Intent Engineering</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">Half-day workshop on encoding values and decision boundaries into agent systems.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$4,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Sovereignty Assessment Workshop <span class="discipline-badge">Evaluation Design</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">Half-day guided sovereignty assessment on your product with your team.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$4,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Sovereignty-Honoring Design</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Half-day training on building products that honor user autonomy. Includes framework, exercises, and recording.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$4,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Child Safety Implementation</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Half-day training on age-gating, consent flows, and data protection for products serving children. Includes code templates and implementation guide.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$4,500</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="mt-lg">Implementation</h3>
    <div class="services-list">
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Specification Engineering Sprint <span class="discipline-badge">Specification Engineering</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">One-week sprint producing agent specifications your team can deploy against.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$5,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Restraint Specification Build</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Define what your agents must refuse, build the refusal infrastructure, and run adversarial testing. 2-4 weeks with your engineering team.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$15,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Trust Architecture Build</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Design and implement identity, memory, governance, and refusal rights across your agent system. 4-8 weeks with your team.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$40,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Ethical AI Architecture</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Full-stack agent governance - multi-agent identity, behavioral specifications, drift monitoring, alignment verification, and operational review cadence.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$75,000+</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Child Safety Build Support</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Hands-on implementation of age gates, parental consent flows, and data protection. Built alongside your engineering team over 2-4 weeks.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$12,000</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="mt-lg">Advisory</h3>
    <div class="services-list">
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Governance Advisory <span class="discipline-badge">Full Practice</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">$5,000/mo: monthly governance reviews, async counsel, specification updates. $15,000/mo: embedded governance partnership with weekly touchpoints, drift monitoring, and incident response.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$5,000 - $15,000/mo</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-muted mt-md" style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
      I focus on technical implementation - not legal advice. For legal interpretation
      of COPPA, GDPR, or other regulations, please consult a qualified attorney.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container text-center">
    <h2>Let's Talk</h2>
    <p>Free 30-minute discovery call. No pitch deck. Just a conversation about where you are and what you need.</p>
    <div class="cta-buttons mt-md">
      <a href="/fit" class="btn">Check Project Fit</a>
      <a href="https://cal.com/cal.com-evoked/discovery-call" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Schedule a Call</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .discipline-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }

  .inertia-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .inertia-grid .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .inertia-grid .card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .discipline-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
  }

  .level-card {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    transition: border-color var(--transition-smooth);
  }

  .level-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-accent);
  }

  .level-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .level-content h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .level-content p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .bridge-text {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* Engagement ladder */
  .ladder {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
  }

  .ladder-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    padding: var(--space-md) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .ladder-step:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .ladder-marker {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 80px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding-top: 2px;
  }

  .ladder-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 100px;
  }

  .ladder-content {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .ladder-content h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .ladder-content p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .ladder-price {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .ladder-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-left: var(--space-sm);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
  }

  /* Services list */
  .services-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .service-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    padding: var(--space-sm) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .service-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .service-name {
    font-weight: 500;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .service-desc {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 200px;
  }

  .service-price {
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-weight: 500;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-left: auto;
  }

  .guarantee {
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-accent);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .guarantee strong {
    color: var(--accent-warm);
  }

  .cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent-warm);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent-glow);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  /* Case study card */
  .case-study-card {
    display: block;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 8px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all var(--transition-smooth);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .case-study-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-accent);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .case-study-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .case-study-collab {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .case-study-collab strong {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .case-study-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .case-study-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .case-study-stats {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .case-study-stats span {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 100px;
  }

  .case-study-link {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .service-item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.25rem;
    }

    .service-price {
      margin-left: 0;
    }

    .level-card {
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .level-number {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .ladder-step {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-xs);
    }

    .ladder-marker {
      width: auto;
    }
  }
</style>
